text: Inglewood is a town in the Taranaki Region of New Zealand's North Island. It is located 16 kilometers south-east of New Plymouth on State Highway 3 and is close to Mount Taranaki. It is a major dairy farming town in the North Island. The town has produced four All Blacks most notably Dave Loveridge. == References == Category:Towns in Taranaki Category:New Plymouth District
title: Inglewood, New Zealand
